Exercises
• Go to https://github.com/ and create a new repository
• Add the README file
• Clone the GitHub repository to your local machine
• Create a new branch and switch to the branch
• Place some (course) files in the repository and add/commit the changes
• Edit the README file with information about the added files
• Include the changes from the branch in the main branch
• Delete the second branch
• Send your changes to GitHub
• Check the commits on the GitHub website

